  "texts": [
    "Despite these promised benefits, there are several limitations and pitfalls to be carefully addressed.",
    "Hence, this study categorizes the challenges and limitations from three different perspectives, namely algorithms, maturity indexes and instruments.",
    "The following subsections discuss in detail some of the relevant challenges faced when applying advanced sensor fusion and AI techniques to agriculture and particularly fruit maturity estimation.",
    "Table 6 Comparative discussion among the ML algorithms Algorithm Actions/features Advantage Disadvantage Application Decision tree Takes decision at every stages based on predefined conditions Simple and easy to interpret Can form a complex tree structure if the number of input features is high Regression and classification For pre-processing, it requires less data Applicable with both numerical and categorical data Poor in stability i.e.",
    "sensitive to noise in the input features Random forest Primarily developed by many Decision Trees One of the best for classification Not efficient as regression model Regression and Classification Can deal with the missing values with an accuracy Does not overfit a model Limited access in model activities Each decision tree offers a classification and random forest picks the highest voted prediction from the collected classifications Can deal with a large volume of data with higher dimensionality Loss of interpretability as the size of the ensemble increases Support vector machine n number of features can be grouped in n dimensional space by hyperplane Efficient in dealing with high-dimensional data Training time can be higher sometimes Regression and classification Memory efficient since it uses subset training points Performance degrades in presence of the overlapping of target classes Naïve bayes Adopts Bayesian theorem Does not require huge volume of data Inefficient in estimation Classification Fast in prediction Applies probabilities in every case and defines new cases based on highest probability outcome Efficient in diagnostic problems K-nearest neighbors Stores all data and predicts the class of a new instance concentrating on the similarity at the nearest neighbours Implementation is simple Highly computational that leads to slow response Regression and classification Efficient in noisy dataset Can work effectively with large dataset Challenging to find a suitable value of k Table 6 (continued) Algorithm Actions/features Advantage Disadvantage Application ANN and derivatives Artificial neurons form layers that receives information from outside Can deal with a large volume of data Black box nature Regression and classification Does not need to be defined the features Requires less statistical training to develop a model These layers are connected through mathematical relations Can detect nonlinear relationships between dependent and independent variables Loss of interpretability as the number of input layers increase Based on the weights in the connections, neurons feed the input data from one layer to another and hence, finally primary input data are construed into information Has good adaptability and anti-noise capacity Prone to overfitting as the number of model parameters increase"
  ]
